1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,420
This is the story of a poor boy.

2
00:00:02,460 --> 00:00:05,280
He had no money, he had no mobile phone,

3
00:00:05,280 --> 00:00:07,940
he had no English books, but still,

4
00:00:08,140 --> 00:00:13,779
he learned to speak English fluently and his life changed.

5
00:00:14,445 --> 00:00:15,844
How did he do it?

6
00:00:16,044 --> 00:00:17,844
Let me tell you his story.

7
00:00:17,965 --> 00:00:19,905
The boy's name was Aman.

8
00:00:19,905 --> 00:00:21,505
He lived in a small village.

9
00:00:21,505 --> 00:00:23,024
His father was a farmer.

10
00:00:23,024 --> 00:00:25,205
His mother worked in people's homes.

11
00:00:25,165 --> 00:00:26,805
They were very poor.

12
00:00:26,764 --> 00:00:29,445
Sometimes, they ate only one meal a day.

13
00:00:30,209 --> 00:00:32,810
Amman worked in the fields after school.

14
00:00:33,089 --> 00:00:35,290
He helped his mother clean houses.

15
00:00:35,250 --> 00:00:38,890
He never complained, but he had one big dream.

16
00:00:39,410 --> 00:00:41,450
Amman wanted to speak English.

17
00:00:41,650 --> 00:00:42,490
Why?

18
00:00:42,449 --> 00:00:45,210
Because in his school, rich boys laughed at him.

19
00:00:45,644 --> 00:00:47,124
They spoke English.

20
00:00:47,085 --> 00:00:48,165
He could not.

21
00:00:48,205 --> 00:00:49,525
He felt small.

22
00:00:49,565 --> 00:00:50,964
He felt stupid.

23
00:00:51,004 --> 00:00:52,645
He felt alone.

24
00:00:52,925 --> 00:00:54,485
But he made a decision.

25
00:00:55,085 --> 00:00:59,444
I will learn English, he said, no matter how hard it is.

26
00:01:00,240 --> 00:01:02,740
A man had no money for English classes.

27
00:01:02,740 --> 00:01:08,520
He had no Internet, but he had one thing, his strong will.

28
00:01:08,880 --> 00:01:11,640
He found old newspapers in the garbage.

29
00:01:11,680 --> 00:01:12,919
He tried to read them.

30
00:01:13,255 --> 00:01:16,895
He listened to English classes from outside the school window.

31
00:01:17,095 --> 00:01:19,854
He wrote down words in a small notebook.

32
00:01:19,975 --> 00:01:22,734
One word, every day.

33
00:01:22,935 --> 00:01:24,715
He used a simple trick.

34
00:01:24,715 --> 00:01:27,054
He spoke to himself in English.

35
00:01:27,370 --> 00:01:29,089
He practiced daily.

36
00:01:29,050 --> 00:01:30,530
He made mistakes.

37
00:01:30,570 --> 00:01:34,050
He laughed at his own English, but he never stopped.

38
00:01:34,330 --> 00:01:37,089
He listened to English songs on old radio.

39
00:01:37,290 --> 00:01:39,970
He watched people's lips when they spoke English.

40
00:01:40,170 --> 00:01:41,169
He copied them.

41
00:01:41,835 --> 00:01:43,954
Slowly, he improved.

42
00:01:44,395 --> 00:01:48,274
After six months, he could say simple sentences.

43
00:01:48,875 --> 00:01:52,914
After one year, he could speak with tourists near his village.

44
00:01:53,910 --> 00:01:55,309
They were surprised.

45
00:01:55,670 --> 00:01:57,149
Aman felt happy.

46
00:01:57,590 --> 00:01:59,390
He was not scared now.

47
00:01:59,590 --> 00:02:01,309
He wanted to speak more.

48
00:02:01,670 --> 00:02:03,929
Now, Aman wanted to help others.

49
00:02:03,929 --> 00:02:08,509
He started teaching English to younger children under a tree for free.

50
00:02:08,975 --> 00:02:12,614
He told them, you don't need money to learn English.

51
00:02:12,655 --> 00:02:16,775
You need two things, time and effort.

52
00:02:17,135 --> 00:02:20,295
One day, a teacher from the city came to his village.

53
00:02:20,255 --> 00:02:22,055
He heard Amman speaking English.

54
00:02:22,470 --> 00:02:23,790
He was shocked.

55
00:02:23,910 --> 00:02:26,350
The teacher helped Aman get a scholarship.

56
00:02:26,550 --> 00:02:28,090
Aman went to college.

57
00:02:28,090 --> 00:02:29,550
He studied English.

58
00:02:29,670 --> 00:02:31,770
He became a teacher.

59
00:02:31,770 --> 00:02:34,090
Today, Aman teaches hundreds of students.

60
00:02:34,090 --> 00:02:35,549
He speaks English every day.

61
00:02:35,615 --> 00:02:37,315
People respect him.

62
00:02:37,315 --> 00:02:44,295
He changed his life with English, without money, without coaching, just with hard work.

63
00:02:44,575 --> 00:02:46,375
Maybe you are like Aman.

64
00:02:46,495 --> 00:02:49,574
Maybe you don't have a lot, but you have a dream.

65
00:02:50,130 --> 00:02:51,850
You can speak English.

66
00:02:52,050 --> 00:02:55,290
You just need to start today.

67
00:02:55,650 --> 00:02:57,290
One word.

68
00:02:57,250 --> 00:02:58,490
One sentence.

69
00:02:58,450 --> 00:02:59,690
One step.

70
00:02:59,730 --> 00:03:03,350
Because your journey is hard, but not impossible.
